If a DFS Transformer is present, we don't run `_fast_permutation_importance` instead running `_slow_permutation_importance`. 
```
    @property
    def _supports_fast_permutation_importance(self):
        has_more_than_one_estimator = (
            sum(isinstance(c, Estimator) for c in self.component_graph) > 1
        )
        _all_components = set(all_components())
        has_custom_components = any(
            c.__class__ not in _all_components for c in self.component_graph
        )
        has_dim_reduction = any(
            isinstance(c, (PCA, LinearDiscriminantAnalysis))
            for c in self.component_graph
        )
        has_dfs = any(isinstance(c, DFSTransformer) for c in self.component_graph)
        return not any(
            [
                has_more_than_one_estimator,
                has_custom_components,
                has_dim_reduction,
                has_dfs,
            ],
        )
```
This is fine for the majority of cases however in the case where we already have all features from DFS present in the pipeline before applying DFS Transformer we really should be running `_fast_permutation_importance`.

Something like this should work
```
    @property
    def _supports_fast_permutation_importance(self):
        has_more_than_one_estimator = (
            sum(isinstance(c, Estimator) for c in self.component_graph) > 1
        )
        _all_components = set(all_components())
        has_custom_components = any(
            c.__class__ not in _all_components for c in self.component_graph
        )
        has_dim_reduction = any(
            isinstance(c, (PCA, LinearDiscriminantAnalysis))
            for c in self.component_graph
        )
        has_dfs = any(isinstance(c, DFSTransformer) for c in self.component_graph)
        if has_dfs:
            dfs_feature_names = [
                name
                for feature in self.component_graph[DFSTransformer.name].features
                for name in feature.get_feature_names()
                if name != self.input_target_name
            ]
            contains_pre_existing_dfs_features = (
                dfs_feature_names == self.input_feature_names[DFSTransformer.name]
            )
        return not any(
            [
                has_more_than_one_estimator,
                has_custom_components,
                has_dim_reduction,
                (has_dfs and not contains_pre_existing_dfs_features),
            ],
        )
```

**Repro**
Run [TS user guide](https://evalml.alteryx.com/en/stable/user_guide/timeseries.html) example, and include ARIMA when running automl. It'll error out on the provided dataset.

