Currently, if a user specifies `mode="long"` using the top level `search()` method, it will only run for the default `AutoMLSearch.search()` run time and does not even make it past the `fast` batches. This issue tracks fixing the logic in `search()` so that if a user specifies `long` it will complete at least the initial long mode batches.

A complication with this issue is the current logic behind `max_batches` and `max_iterations`. My initial understanding was that by specifying `max_batches` AutoMLSearch will end after exactly n batches. However, the actual stopping criterion is based off of a calculation of max_pipelines and the length of allowed pipelines. This works for the current algorithm and its ensembling implementation but does not work with the new default algorithm. This might be resolved by #2656.

